description: Almost a full loop around the lake is possible on shared bike paths including the Tuggerah Lakes Cycleway, and several kilometers of bush trails through Wyrrabalong National Park.

markers.description: Get the train to Tuggerah using transportnsw.info.
Exit the station on the carpark side and follow Bryant Dr.
Follow Bryant Dr right around the corner.
Cross Wyong Rd at the pedestrian crossing to the left of the roundabout.
After crossing follow the footpath along Wyong Rd to the left.
After the bridge over Ourimbah Creek cross Wyong Road into the park on the other side.
Follow the footpath through the park to the shops.
There are amenities a the shopping centre.
From the shopping centre carpark cross Chittaway Rd at the roundabout and follow James Watt Dr straight on.
Follow the Chittaway Wetland Walk to the left.
Cross Lakedge Ave and follow the footpath into Chittaway Bay Lions Park to the playground.
From the playground follow the shared path along the foreshore.
There are toilets at the Bluebell Park and amenities across the road.
There is a cafe along the road.
Cross Azads Footpath Bridge to the left.
There is a toilet block at the Killarney Vale Foreshore.
Cross the bridge over Saltwater Creek.
From the bridge follow the footpath past the boatramp.
There is a toilet block near Parry's Jetty.
The first chance at a long jetty.
markers.title: All Jetties Short and Long: Parry's Jetty
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Continue along the foreshore footpath from Parry's Jetty.
Continue along the foreshore footpath from Watkin's Jetty.
It's not as long, but also not as busy.
markers.title: All Jetties Short and Long: Watkin's Jetty
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: There is a toilet block at Long Jetty.
Walking down this endless jetty feels like being envelloped by the void.
markers.title: All Jetties Short and Long: Long Jetty
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Continue along the foreshore footpath from Long Jetty.
Follow the sign to Picnic Point to the left.
There is a toilet block at Picnic Point.
From Picnic Point follow the footpath right along the foreshore towards the bridge.
Follow the footpath under the bridge.
There are public toilets right after the bridge.
There are amenities along The Entrance foreshore.
Get the bus to/from The Entrance using transportnsw.info.
From the roundabout at the bridge follow the onramp onto the bridge.
Cross Tuggerah Entrance over the bridge.
On the other side of the bridge cross Wilfred Barrett Drive and follow the footpath into Terilbah Reserve.
Follow the foreshore footpath to the Sensory Garden and then the boat ramp.
There is a toilet block at the carpark.
Cross the carpark access road and follow the foreshore footpath to the right.
At the intersection follow the Magenta Bike Path to the left.
Cross the intersection and continue on the Magnta Bike Path.
Follow the bikepath though the bushland reserve.
Follow the bike path along the Central Coast Hwy.
There may be detours along the Central Coast Hwy for unfinished sections of the bike path.
From the carpark follow the Lilly Pilly Loop Trail away from the highway into Wyrrabalong National Park.
Follow the Lilly Pilly Loop Trail through the rainforest section of the park.
The first of four biomes of Wyrrabalong. It is a rare treat to find a remnant stretch of rainforest.
markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Rainforest
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: At the shorefront follow the Lilly Pilly Loop trail to the right.
From the shorefront the trail ascends to the dune tops.
At the intersection continue straight along the Redgum Trail.
The second of four biomes of Wyrrabalong. Most striking when the sun is low enough to make the red gums light up bright.
markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Red Gum Forest
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the intersection follow the Wetlands Trail to the left.
The third of four biomes of Wyrranalong. The fourth you'll have to find somewhere else entirely.
markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Wetlands
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the end of the Wetlands Trail continue straight along Evans Rd past the tourist parks.
At the intersection after the tourist parks follow Oleander St to the left.
At the intersection follow Wattle St to the right.
Cross the reserve and follow Belbowrie St to the left.
From the corner of Belbowrie St follow the footpath right along Canton Beach Foreshore.
There is a toilet block at Canton Beach Foreshore.
From the roundabout at the end of the foreshore path follow Moss Ave to the left.
Follow Pearce Ave to the right to the community centre.
From the community centre cross the carpark to the shops.
From the shops cross the carpark to the exit on the left.
There are amenities at Toukley Village.
From the carpark exist follow Yaralla Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow Main Rd to the left. There is a toilet block in Toukley Gardens across the road.
Follow the footpath across the Toukley Bridge.
Cross Toukley Bridge and continue straight along Wallarah Rd.
There is a toilet block at Wallarah Point Peace Park.
There are amenities at the Gorokan shops.
After the shops follow Lakeview Ave to the left.
At the intersection follow Lett St to the right.
At the intersection follow Leichhardt Rd to the left.
Cross through the reserve on the right side of Brennon St.
From the reserve continue straight along Marks Rd.
Follow the footpath into Craigie Park to the left.
Cross the bridge into Craigie Park.
Follow the footpath through Craigie Park.
There's a toilet block at the carpark.
From the carpark follow Tuggerawong Rd to the left.
There are amenities at the Wyongah Takeout.
Follow Prawn Beach Ln to the left.
From the end of Prawn Beach Ln follow the Tuggerawong Shared Pathway to the right.
Follow the Tuggerawong Shared Pathway along the foreshore.
From the end of the Tuggerawong Shared Pathway follow Palmet St to the right.
From the intersection follow Wolseley Ave to the left. Take the bus here if the lack of footpaths onwards is a concern.
Get the bus from Rocky Point using transportnsw.info.
Follow the shoulder of Wolseley Ave to the riverside. There is a toilet block at the corner.
From the corner of Wolseley Ave follow the shoulder of the road to the right.
At the intersection follow McDonagh Rd to the right.
From the intersection with Panonia Rd continue straight on Boyce Ave.
From the intersection with Warner Ave continue following Boyce Ave to the left.
Follow the footpath along Boyce Ave past the sports fields.
At the intersection cross Howarth St and follow the carpark right to the station.
Plan your return trip from Wyong at transportnsw.info.
